snippet: Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton reached out to President Mohamed Morsi but appeared constrained by reluctance to address his struggle with Egypt’s generals.
abstract: Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton arrives in Egypt for meetings with Pres Mohamed Morsi and Field Marshal Mohamed Hussein Tantawi, the chief of the still-dominant military council; expresses support for the country's transition to civilian rule, but seems reluctant to address Morsi's power struggles with Egypt's generals.
lead_paragraph: Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton reached out to President Mohamed Morsi but appeared constrained by reluctance to address his struggle with Egypt’s generals.
